## Error Handling

### Error Types

{{if eq .Language "go"}}
The client provides utility functions to identify different types of errors:

```go
if err != nil {
    switch {
    case {{.Package}}.IsToolError(err):
        // Handle tool-specific errors
    case {{.Package}}.IsConnectionError(err):
        // Handle connection errors
    case {{.Package}}.IsTimeoutError(err):
        // Handle timeout errors
    default:
        // Handle other errors
    }
}
```

### Retry Logic

```go
err = client.ExecuteWithRetry(ctx, func() error {
    return client.Ping(ctx)
}, 3)
```

### Timeout Handling

```go
ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 30*time.Second)
defer cancel()

result, err := client.SomeTool(ctx, input)
if err != nil {
    if {{.Package}}.IsTimeoutError(err) {
        // Handle timeout
    }
}
```
{{end}}

